WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.135 --> 00:00:06.129
<i>Carroll was convicted in 2004 for
the murders of 14 young women.</i>

2
00:00:06.306 --> 00:00:09.743
The warden granted Joe Carroll's
request for a transfer. He's leaving.

3
00:00:09.910 --> 00:00:12.903
Joe's not in the transport
vehicle. Where the hell is he?

4
00:00:14.381 --> 00:00:18.148
- Joe's free. now I get locked up.
- Protective custody. Better if I don't know.

5
00:00:18.318 --> 00:00:21.482
- Quantico sent in a new guy.
- Nick Donovan. top of the food chain.

6
00:00:21.655 --> 00:00:24.022
This investigation
starts at my desk now.

7
00:00:24.224 --> 00:00:26.784
Joe Carroll. How
the hell are you. heh?

8
00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:29.288
- I'm Roderick.
- Ugh.

9
00:00:29.463 --> 00:00:31.364
Emma. why did you
leave us? Emma!

10
00:00:31.798 --> 00:00:34.324
- Any word from Jacob and Paul?
- They haven't called.

11
00:00:34.501 --> 00:00:36.527
Hang on. I'm gonna
get us some help.

12
00:00:36.737 --> 00:00:37.864
Thank you.

13
00:00:38.038 --> 00:00:40.507
- I love my wife.
- She's not here.

14
00:00:41.241 --> 00:00:45.076
Losing Claire must sting. but I
have an idea where we can find her.

15
00:00:45.245 --> 00:00:48.374
- Agent Weston. tell us where Claire is.
- Ah. I don't know anything.

16
00:00:48.549 --> 00:00:51.451
Claire's location. He's the only
one who knows where Claire is.

17
00:00:51.618 --> 00:00:53.348
- Everyone's waiting.
- What for?

18
00:00:53.554 --> 00:00:55.182
For you.

19
00:00:56.056 --> 00:00:58.321
Good morning. everybody.

20
00:00:59.693 --> 00:01:02.629
<i>How did Joe Carroll escape in
a helicopter in broad daylight?</i>

21
00:01:02.796 --> 00:01:05.960
Carroll's people infiltrated the
prison. Warden was compromised.

22
00:01:06.133 --> 00:01:08.762
<i>How many people are
part of Carroll's cult?</i>

23
00:01:08.936 --> 00:01:11.906
Early evidence suggested
somewhere under 12...

24
00:01:12.072 --> 00:01:15.770
but. uh. in light of Carroll's recent
escape. tactical resources. manpower...

25
00:01:15.943 --> 00:01:18.640
- could be upwards of 100.
<i>- How did you arrive at that?</i>

26
00:01:18.879 --> 00:01:22.475
Carroll's visitors log in prison
contained 47 false identities.

27
00:01:22.649 --> 00:01:26.780
And his Internet usage. although heavily
encrypted. suggested twice that many.

28
00:01:26.954 --> 00:01:28.445
<i>That's a guess at best. agent.</i>

29
00:01:28.622 --> 00:01:31.251
<i>We looking for a cult compound
like Waco or Jonestown?</i>

30
00:01:31.458 --> 00:01:35.054
Yes. we believe there to
be some sort of safe haven.

31
00:01:35.262 --> 00:01:36.958
<i>But you don't
know where that is.</i>

32
00:01:37.864 --> 00:01:39.992
No. we don't.

33
00:01:42.102 --> 00:01:46.631
Our working theory is that it's
within a three-state radius of Virginia.

34
00:01:46.840 --> 00:01:48.151
<i>Let me get this straight.</i>

35
00:01:48.175 --> 00:01:51.168
<i>There's an organized
gathering of dozens of killers.</i>

36
00:01:51.345 --> 00:01:53.041
<i>And you have no
idea where they are?</i>

37
00:01:53.213 --> 00:01:57.116
Can I just remind everyone that
this is a briefing and not an inquisition?

38
00:01:57.284 --> 00:02:00.049
<i>Who are the people he
recruits? Can't all be serial killers.</i>

39
00:02:00.220 --> 00:02:01.950
He recruits from
all walks of life.

40
00:02:02.122 --> 00:02:06.082
<i>Housewives. teachers.
accountants. military. law enforcement.</i>

41
00:02:06.259 --> 00:02:09.787
<i>All of whom fit the personality types
associated with cult susceptibility.</i>

42
00:02:09.963 --> 00:02:13.263
- Empty. lost. maladjusted...
<i>- To full-blown psychopaths.</i>

43
00:02:13.433 --> 00:02:15.902
<i>The acolytes we've
encountered have run the gamut...</i>

44
00:02:16.069 --> 00:02:18.595
from visionary to
hedonistic one-time killers...

45
00:02:18.772 --> 00:02:20.900
mission-oriented
killers. fans of killers.

46
00:02:21.074 --> 00:02:24.909
<i>Mr. Hardy. an agent was captured
and assaulted by cult members.</i>

47
00:02:25.078 --> 00:02:28.105
<i>- Was he able to identify his captors?</i>
- That agent. Mike Weston?

48
00:02:28.281 --> 00:02:31.445
We have a sketch artist standing
by for the moment he's conscious.

49
00:02:31.618 --> 00:02:34.588
<i>And his cult? Have you identified
their religion or manifesto?</i>

50
00:02:34.755 --> 00:02:37.657
<i>Both a novelist
and a professor...</i>

51
00:02:37.858 --> 00:02:42.023
Carroll's using literary themes found
in the works of gothic romanticism.

52
00:02:42.229 --> 00:02:44.721
<i>All that we see or seem...</i>

53
00:02:45.666 --> 00:02:49.569
is but a dream within a dream.

54
00:02:50.003 --> 00:02:52.973
And that is what this
moment is for me.

55
00:02:53.140 --> 00:02:58.306
He's speaking to his subjects with
the promise of elevating their lives.

56
00:02:59.513 --> 00:03:01.505
Through death.
one experiences life.

57
00:03:01.682 --> 00:03:03.014
<i>I will never forget...</i>

58
00:03:04.651 --> 00:03:08.019
what you have all done for me.

59
00:03:08.221 --> 00:03:11.020
The sacrifices you have made.

60
00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:14.389
But now the time
has come for you.

61
00:03:14.594 --> 00:03:18.895
By his own admission Carroll has engaged
his followers to write their own chapters.

62
00:03:19.066 --> 00:03:22.366
To become part of this
novel that he's writing.

63
00:03:22.536 --> 00:03:26.974
I want to hear from each
and every one of you.

64
00:03:27.474 --> 00:03:32.003
Tell me what inspires you.

65
00:03:32.546 --> 00:03:34.879
I need your help...

66
00:03:35.048 --> 00:03:39.543
to finish our story.

67
00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:43.657
He's united with his people. He will
do something to ignite them to action.

68
00:03:43.824 --> 00:03:47.192
I see it in your eyes.
I know you are ready.

69
00:03:49.296 --> 00:03:52.460
It's time for him to tell
the next part of his story.

70
00:03:54.301 --> 00:03:56.293
And so we begin.

71
00:04:04.277 --> 00:04:05.745
That didn't go well.

72
00:04:05.912 --> 00:04:08.040
Uh. too many people have died.

73
00:04:08.215 --> 00:04:10.116
It's a PR nightmare.

74
00:04:10.283 --> 00:04:12.616
- Gotta blame someone.
- Agent Parker.

75
00:04:12.786 --> 00:04:14.618
I just heard from Franklin.

76
00:04:15.756 --> 00:04:17.520
Will you excuse us?

77
00:04:19.459 --> 00:04:21.325
I'll wait in the car.

78
00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:26.794
Am I out? I know they're
discussing it. Just tell me.

79
00:04:26.967 --> 00:04:29.766
No. but they are taking the
operation and control to D.C.

80
00:04:30.270 --> 00:04:31.670
Where does that leave me?

81
00:04:33.039 --> 00:04:36.100
Everyone recognizes that Ryan
Hardy is integral to all of this.

82
00:04:36.276 --> 00:04:37.642
But he's a wild card.

83
00:04:37.844 --> 00:04:39.972
We want you to stay
on. hold his hand.

84
00:04:40.847 --> 00:04:44.841
You'll keep your task force
here and continue to report to me.

85
00:04:47.187 --> 00:04:48.951
Understood.

86
00:05:47.347 --> 00:05:49.248
Jacob.

87
00:05:50.750 --> 00:05:52.309
Mom.

88
00:05:54.254 --> 00:05:58.988
For my chapter. I thought I...

89
00:05:59.926 --> 00:06:03.488
Uh. I'm sorry. heh. I've been
working on this forever. heh.

90
00:06:03.697 --> 00:06:06.565
I'm just so nervous
with you here. heh.

91
00:06:06.733 --> 00:06:08.224
Um. where was I?

92
00:06:08.401 --> 00:06:10.131
Uh. yes. my chapter.

93
00:06:10.570 --> 00:06:12.903
It's okay. Hey. relax.

94
00:06:14.274 --> 00:06:17.267
- Come on. shake it out. Shake it out.
- Ah. okay. heh.

95
00:06:22.515 --> 00:06:24.074
Thank you for seeing me.

96
00:06:25.452 --> 00:06:27.944
I've been wanting to
visit for so long now.

97
00:06:28.154 --> 00:06:32.922
- I must seem like some groupie to you...
- No. No. Amanda. no.

98
00:06:33.093 --> 00:06:36.063
I found your letters
really quite moving.

99
00:06:36.663 --> 00:06:38.222
I'm glad to finally meet you.

100
00:06:38.431 --> 00:06:42.061
And you wrote
in your last one...

101
00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:44.033
that something had
happened? What?

102
00:06:44.204 --> 00:06:47.470
Yes. but I couldn't
write it in a letter.

103
00:06:49.175 --> 00:06:52.407
Let me guess. your husband.

104
00:06:52.612 --> 00:06:54.103
You know he was cheating on me.

105
00:06:54.281 --> 00:06:56.307
That bony-ass thing
he works with. Lindsay.

106
00:06:56.483 --> 00:07:00.420
The one with the huge fake things.
Right under my nose. in my bed.

107
00:07:00.587 --> 00:07:02.419
I could smell it on my sheets.

108
00:07:02.589 --> 00:07:04.615
I knew you had your suspicions.

109
00:07:04.791 --> 00:07:07.761
You wrote in a letter:

110
00:07:08.461 --> 00:07:11.397
"Insist on happiness."

111
00:07:13.900 --> 00:07:17.928
So I took a shotgun
to both of them.

112
00:07:18.805 --> 00:07:22.333
My daddy was big on
gaming. He could hunt anything.

113
00:07:22.509 --> 00:07:24.978
I know my way around animals.

114
00:07:25.145 --> 00:07:28.343
So I went to a hardware
store and bought a hatchet...

115
00:07:28.515 --> 00:07:31.110
electric hacksaw. some
ammonia. and a bucket.

116
00:07:31.318 --> 00:07:33.412
It took a few days
to bag them up.

117
00:07:33.586 --> 00:07:36.954
Then I drove to Florida and dumped
them in a swamp and drove here.

118
00:07:37.590 --> 00:07:39.616
They're gonna find some pieces.

119
00:07:39.826 --> 00:07:43.763
They can DNA and <i>CSI</i>
that stuff. They'll come for me.

120
00:07:44.798 --> 00:07:47.324
Do you have to go
back to Oklahoma?

121
00:07:47.534 --> 00:07:52.370
I don't have
anywhere to go. Joe.

122
00:07:54.941 --> 00:07:56.807
I have a friend.

123
00:07:56.977 --> 00:07:59.173
His name is Roderick. heh.

124
00:07:59.612 --> 00:08:03.549
He's been known to
help other friends of mine.

125
00:08:04.484 --> 00:08:08.251
I'm sure he'd be able to
give you a place to stay.

126
00:08:12.325 --> 00:08:14.794
You love your wife.

127
00:08:15.628 --> 00:08:16.960
I know you want her back.

128
00:08:17.864 --> 00:08:21.198
And I want that for you. Joe.

129
00:08:22.802 --> 00:08:28.503
I want my chapter to
have a happy ending.

130
00:08:32.078 --> 00:08:33.376
Go on.

131
00:08:41.654 --> 00:08:44.522
- Jacob.
- What?

132
00:08:46.993 --> 00:08:48.859
He's my friend.
Mom. and he's hurt.

133
00:08:49.062 --> 00:08:50.553
I recognize him.

134
00:08:50.730 --> 00:08:53.199
Your faces are plastered
all over the news.

135
00:08:53.400 --> 00:08:54.993
You're a wanted fugitive.

136
00:08:55.168 --> 00:08:58.366
- Kidnapping. murder?
- I never killed anybody. Mom.

137
00:08:58.538 --> 00:09:00.166
- The FBI said you did.
- I haven't.

138
00:09:00.340 --> 00:09:03.504
They say you're involved with
that serial killer. Part of a cult?

139
00:09:03.676 --> 00:09:05.668
I didn't say that
I was innocent.

140
00:09:07.213 --> 00:09:10.342
- Why are you here?
- Because it's impossible at home.

141
00:09:10.517 --> 00:09:13.749
There are federal agents
patrolling our house.

142
00:09:13.953 --> 00:09:15.785
Reporters are following
your father to work.

143
00:09:17.924 --> 00:09:20.120
Oh. well. that's a bummer.

144
00:09:20.326 --> 00:09:21.555
Poor guy.

145
00:09:23.830 --> 00:09:26.390
Help me understand this. Jacob.

146
00:09:27.967 --> 00:09:31.131
I'm your mother and I love
you. but I don't understand this.

147
00:09:37.143 --> 00:09:39.942
I don't think that
I can explain.

148
00:09:54.994 --> 00:09:57.225
No. detective. I'm
staring at it right now.

149
00:09:57.397 --> 00:10:00.265
That's not Paul Torres.
that's not Jacob Wells.

150
00:10:00.433 --> 00:10:02.902
No. absolutely sure.

151
00:10:03.069 --> 00:10:04.731
Neither man.

152
00:10:04.904 --> 00:10:06.566
No. not a waste
of my time. Thanks.

153
00:10:06.773 --> 00:10:10.301
Complete waste of my time. This is
the chief homicide detective in Dallas.

154
00:10:10.510 --> 00:10:12.172
I'm sorry. I let it through.

155
00:10:12.345 --> 00:10:13.369
He was convinced.

156
00:10:14.814 --> 00:10:17.374
Ryan Hardy. CARROLL <i>Hello. Ryan.</i>

157
00:10:18.651 --> 00:10:21.246
- What can I do for you. Joe?
<i>- I just wanted to see...</i>

158
00:10:21.421 --> 00:10:23.287
<i>how your friend.
Weston. was doing. eh.</i>

159
00:10:23.490 --> 00:10:25.959
I heard that he
took quite a beating.

160
00:10:26.693 --> 00:10:29.959
- He's expected to make a full recovery.
- Oh.

161
00:10:30.130 --> 00:10:31.962
No. that's good to hear.

162
00:10:32.665 --> 00:10:34.691
Sorry about your
friends. though.

163
00:10:34.901 --> 00:10:36.199
They're kind of dead.

164
00:10:36.436 --> 00:10:39.463
That's okay. I have more. heh.

165
00:10:42.108 --> 00:10:44.441
So. what do you want. Joe?

166
00:10:45.445 --> 00:10:49.815
You know. just to chat.
I'm feeling a little bit down.

167
00:10:50.517 --> 00:10:52.042
Tell me...

168
00:10:52.619 --> 00:10:54.713
do you miss Claire. Ryan?

169
00:10:54.921 --> 00:10:56.480
I know I do.

170
00:10:56.656 --> 00:11:01.560
<i>Ironically. you're the only person who
really understands how I feel at the moment.</i>

171
00:11:01.794 --> 00:11:04.662
Being that we both
love the same woman.

172
00:11:05.331 --> 00:11:09.132
Why is love so punishing. Ryan?

173
00:11:09.335 --> 00:11:11.463
- Get something.
- He's on a satellite phone.

174
00:11:11.638 --> 00:11:14.005
- Sends me to Singapore.
- Homeland can intercept.

175
00:11:14.174 --> 00:11:18.077
<i>Love's elation always
seems to turn to pain.</i>

176
00:11:18.311 --> 00:11:21.748
How true the adage
"love hurts." huh?

177
00:11:22.482 --> 00:11:28.979
Tell me. how much hurt
can one man endure. Ryan?

178
00:11:30.757 --> 00:11:35.024
Uh. at what point does he break?

179
00:11:35.895 --> 00:11:37.227
You must let me know.

180
00:11:49.342 --> 00:11:53.609
I can't remember. what is good here?
Did I get the hamburger steak last time?

181
00:11:53.846 --> 00:11:55.371
You liked it. didn't love it.

182
00:11:55.548 --> 00:11:57.710
Heh. it's fine. Will you order?

183
00:11:57.884 --> 00:12:00.820
Uh. no onions. gravy on the
fries. I'm gonna wash my hands.

184
00:12:16.536 --> 00:12:18.767
I'm sorry. can I help you. heh?

185
00:12:19.372 --> 00:12:22.900
Yes. you can. I need you
to give someone a message.

186
00:12:23.109 --> 00:12:25.408
I'm sorry. do I know you?

187
00:12:25.578 --> 00:12:27.706
What are you doing?
What's in your hands?

188
00:12:27.880 --> 00:12:30.873
Oh. it's nothing really. I need
you to do something for me.

189
00:12:31.050 --> 00:12:35.545
It's like a favor. There's
this man named Ryan Hardy.

190
00:12:36.022 --> 00:12:38.150
I think you have
the wrong table.

191
00:12:38.324 --> 00:12:39.519
This is important.

192
00:12:40.560 --> 00:12:45.294
You need to tell Ryan
Hardy that sometimes...

193
00:12:45.798 --> 00:12:48.358
love hurts. Can
you remember that?

194
00:12:48.534 --> 00:12:50.560
- Heh. hey.
- Hi.

195
00:12:50.737 --> 00:12:52.501
- Who is this?
- I don't know.

196
00:12:52.672 --> 00:12:55.403
- She has something in her hands.
- What do you have there?

197
00:12:55.575 --> 00:12:57.567
Customized 24-inch
pressurized spear gun.

198
00:12:57.744 --> 00:12:59.440
Mainly used for
deep-sea fishing.

199
00:12:59.612 --> 00:13:01.308
Heh. what are you
gonna do with that?

200
00:13:02.982 --> 00:13:06.646
I'm sorry. I didn't
mean to laugh.

201
00:13:06.853 --> 00:13:08.549
I'm gonna try it out.

202
00:13:08.721 --> 00:13:12.419
- Unh!
- Oh. my God! Oh. my God. help!

203
00:13:12.625 --> 00:13:14.924
- She's bleeding!
- Don't forget what I told you.

204
00:13:15.128 --> 00:13:18.587
- Oh. my God. help me! Somebody help me!
- Thank you.

205
00:13:18.798 --> 00:13:21.143
Oh. my God. she's bleeding.
- Oh. God. help me!

206
00:13:21.167 --> 00:13:22.226
She's bleeding.

207
00:13:22.402 --> 00:13:24.962
Help me! Somebody help!

208
00:13:44.023 --> 00:13:48.654
And then she just
walked right out the door.

209
00:13:49.128 --> 00:13:53.589
She said. "Tell Ryan
Hardy that love hurts."

210
00:13:53.900 --> 00:13:57.894
I don't understand. why
would she kill Claire?

211
00:14:00.340 --> 00:14:03.401
Excuse me. ma'am.
hi. Uh. your friend...

212
00:14:04.043 --> 00:14:05.739
Claire Dobkins. was she married?

213
00:14:07.246 --> 00:14:10.808
She was separated. Why?

214
00:14:10.983 --> 00:14:12.349
What was her maiden name?

215
00:14:14.387 --> 00:14:15.878
It was Matthews.

216
00:14:20.026 --> 00:14:21.050
Hey.

217
00:14:21.427 --> 00:14:23.089
- Make sure Claire is safe.
- She is.

218
00:14:23.262 --> 00:14:25.356
We moved her location
after Weston's attack.

219
00:14:25.531 --> 00:14:27.329
- Check again. confirm it.
- She's safe.

220
00:14:27.500 --> 00:14:30.732
- She can't turn on the TV. This'll kill her.
- You're over-reacting.

221
00:14:30.937 --> 00:14:34.533
- Take away all media access. Just do it.
- Let them do their job.

222
00:14:36.442 --> 00:14:38.172
Hey. Are you okay?

223
00:14:38.344 --> 00:14:41.508
I'm fine. I'm good.
I'm good. it's just...

224
00:14:42.014 --> 00:14:45.542
Joe said. "How much
hurt can one man endure?"

225
00:14:46.219 --> 00:14:47.687
He's trying to break you.

226
00:14:47.854 --> 00:14:50.085
By targeting women
with his wife's name.

227
00:14:50.256 --> 00:14:53.522
I mean. how many Claire
Matthews are out there?

228
00:15:00.733 --> 00:15:03.794
- Your wound is infected.
- Can you help me?

229
00:15:03.970 --> 00:15:05.529
You're a nurse. right?

230
00:15:06.105 --> 00:15:09.041
- Jacob said you were a nurse.
- I was.

231
00:15:09.208 --> 00:15:10.574
I'm not anymore.

232
00:15:12.745 --> 00:15:14.077
Who are you calling?

233
00:15:14.680 --> 00:15:17.775
- Who are you calling?
- I'm leaving another message for Emma.

234
00:15:18.684 --> 00:15:20.983
She's not gonna call you back.

235
00:15:21.888 --> 00:15:24.221
Don't you get it? She left us.

236
00:15:25.258 --> 00:15:26.886
She left us to die.

237
